                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>« <a href="/news-01-2016">January 2016</a> | <span style="text-decoration: underline;">February 2016</span> | <a href="/news-03-2016">March 2016</a> »</strong></p>
</div>
<p>Welcome to this installment of site news, the only news outlet that you follow that can afford to not be updated on time and get away with it! This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month, and fancontent for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</p>
<h3 id="toc0"><span>On-Site News</span></h3>
<h4 id="toc1"><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>The featured articles for this month are <a href="/scp-2314">SCP-2314</a> (&quot;Проект Стебельчатый Глаз&quot;) by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-nikolaus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1691109); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1691109&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Dr Nikolaus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1691109)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-nikolaus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1691109); return false;">Dr Nikolaus</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/crayne" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1346995); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1346995&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Crayne" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1346995)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/crayne" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1346995); return false;">Crayne</a></span>, and <a href="/loyal-to-the-cause">Loyal to the Cause</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/erku" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(600767); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=600767&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Erku" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=600767)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/erku" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(600767); return false;">Erku</a></span>. One's about a roundworm that suppresses your immune system in unexpected ways, and the other is about a Foundation employee being put to the test. Check them out!</li>
<li>The featured articles from last month were <a href="/scp-1431">SCP-1431</a> (&quot;Scavenger Hunt!&quot;) by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uglyflower" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1741178); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1741178&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="UglyFlower" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1741178)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uglyflower" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1741178); return false;">UglyFlower</a></span> and <a href="/a-visitation">A Visitation</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/assertiveroland" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(459975); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=459975&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="AssertiveRoland" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=459975)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/assertiveroland" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(459975); return false;">AssertiveRoland</a></span>. One's about an odd scavenger hunt that gives you some&#8230; odd goals to complete, and the other is about a wealthy man who wants to chat about an infamous book of his. Check them out if you missed them!</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc2"><span>Rest of the News</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="/mobile-task-force-contest">Mobile Task Force Contest</a> posting period has ended, and we've got a range of great entries! I'm very happy with how the contest turned out, and hopefully, all of you are as well. Go peruse the entries!</li>
<li>The <a href="/foundation-tales">tales</a> hub has been reorganized! The layout will be a bit different, and updates twice a week instead of automatically, but should still be as accessible as before. You can also now browse tale entries by title, in addition to still being able to browse by author and by year.</li>
<li>The 2nd Annual <a href="/scpfmmdbc-hub">SCP Foundation March Madness</a> competition will be starting very soon! Guts, glory, excitement, pointless bracketing! Everything you love about <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NCAA_March_Madness_%28CBS/Turner%29">March Madness</a>, now SCP-ified!</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p>Missing out on articles? Enjoy a recap on the articles from the past month. Because of how the past month has turned out, I figure it'd be only sensible to separate contest articles from non-contest articles for your ease of reading. Let's start out with non-contest articles. Enjoy!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Non-contest&nbsp;articles!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Non-contest&nbsp;articles!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h3 id="toc3"><span>Week of February 1st</span></h3>
<p>From werebricks to Misters to sloths, oh my! Lots of strange anomalies to sink our teeth into.</p>
<h4 id="toc4"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2537">SCP-2537</a> (&quot;Werebricks&quot;) - Brick by brick, these werebricks are assembling a bridge to an unknown and mysterious place. But I mean&#8230; they're werebricks! That's a trip in of itself! Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1735681&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="TwistedGears" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1735681)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;">TwistedGears</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2284">SCP-2284</a> (&quot;Mr. Lie&quot;) - Everything Mr. Lie says is objectively true. You have no reason to disbelieve him. Would you ever disbelieve someone who could ever lie? Of course not. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1735681&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="TwistedGears" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1735681)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;">TwistedGears</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2774">SCP-2774</a> (&quot;The Slow Burn Sloth&quot;) - The greatest prison is the body, where only the mind can control itself. Colorblindness is recommended. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/moohab" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1893193); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1893193&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Moohab" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1893193)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/moohab" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1893193); return false;">Moohab</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2318">SCP-2318</a> (&quot;Awake in the Infinite Cold&quot;) - There are places in this world that defy explanation, that abhor understanding, that exist within a vacuum of absolution. These are the quiet places, forgotten and dark, and they go on forever. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;">djkaktus</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-396">SCP-396</a> (&quot;And Suddenly, Chair&quot;) - This cute little chair just wants to lend a helping seat to people! The only downside is that it can be a bit too eager to displace itself at times, and can cause some issues. Like displacing the Pope's throne. <a href="http://scpclassic.wikidot.com/scp-396">Originally written</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-kondraki" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(223359); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=223359&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Dr Kondraki" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=223359)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-kondraki" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(223359); return false;">Dr Kondraki</a></span>, rewritten by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/roget" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1229263); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1229263&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Roget" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1229263)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/roget" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1229263); return false;">Roget</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2346">SCP-2346</a> (&quot;Die Bescheidene&quot;) - A long-forgotten ship, now lying at the bottom of the ocean. It moves more and more, beckoning divers to pilot the ship. Where to? That's for you to board the ship and find out. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kmx37r" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1916215); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1916215&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="kmx37r" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1916215)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kmx37r" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1916215); return false;">kmx37r</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-wtf-j">SCP-WTF-J</a> (&quot;The Worst&quot;) - Take one part fascism, five parts Kate Bush, a few nuns, and [REDACTED], and what do you get? <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/daveyoufool" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2034230); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2034230&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="daveyoufool" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2034230)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/daveyoufool" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2034230); return false;">daveyoufool</a></span> invites you to review the procedures for yourself.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc5"><span>Tales</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/on-the-efficiency-of-various-postal-services">On The Efficiency Of Various Postal Services</a> - A series of letters concerning <a href="/scp-2699">SCP-2699</a> and the mysterious employers surrounding it. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eta-carinae" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2110706); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2110706&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Eta Carinae" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2110706)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eta-carinae" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2110706); return false;">Eta Carinae</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/remembrance-of-walking">Remembrance Of Walking</a> - He walked. He could only remember walking, and he will continue to walk, traversing the boardwalk empire. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drewbear" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(301632); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=301632&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Drewbear" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=301632)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drewbear" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(301632); return false;">Drewbear</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/on-seabirds-and-sleep">On Seabirds And Sleep</a> - I dunno what this means. But, well, y'know. Poets don't write to be understood. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1379080&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Randomini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1379080)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;">Randomini</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="toc6"><span>Week of February 8th</span></h3>
<p>CATS AND TRASH TRASHCATS TRASH AND CATS CATTRASH</p>
<h4 id="toc7"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-796">SCP-796</a> (&quot;River Cat&quot;) - &quot;He is quiet and small, he is black/From his ears to the tip of his tail;/He can creep through the tiniest crack,/He can walk on the narrowest rail.&quot; -T. S. Eliot, <em>Old Possum's Book Of Practical Cats</em>. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/minmin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(560062); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=560062&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="minmin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=560062)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/minmin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(560062); return false;">minmin</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2493">SCP-2493</a> (&quot;One Man's Garbage&quot;) - Trade an endless supply of rubbish for advanced technology? Yes please. Contain a man made of antimatter safely on the moon? Sure. Destroy your entire universe because you couldn't be bothered recycling? Preferably not. Recycled by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-ike" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1618170); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1618170&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Jack Ike" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1618170)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-ike" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1618170); return false;">Jack Ike</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-008-j">SCP-008-J</a> (&quot;Geoff&quot;) - Oh hey, it's you!<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup> I was just cleaning up around here, and noticed that I saw you before. How have you been?<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-2')">2</a></sup> Hey, do you have any social media? We gotta get in touch more often. Tell <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/domeacolyte" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2230092); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2230092&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="DomeAcolyte" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2230092)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/domeacolyte" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2230092); return false;">DomeAcolyte</a></span> that I said thanks for connecting us.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-3" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-3')">3</a></sup></li>
<li><a href="/scp-2321">SCP-2321</a> (&quot;Foor Th'luv Uv God Doont Yuuz It&quot;) - It came from the future to make the present our past! But some dumbass broke it and now it's junk. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1304786&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="TL333s" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1304786)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;">TL333s</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2917">SCP-2917</a> (&quot;USS Enterprise&quot;) - All aboard the <em>SCPS Enterprise</em>! She updates herself to match any modern boat and give them a run for their money! With it, the Foundation shall be ever-so vigilant on the seas! A translation of <a href="http://ko.scp-wiki.net/scp-217-ko">SCP-217-KO</a>. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/major-gordon" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3021385); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3021385&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Major Gordon" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3021385)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/major-gordon" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3021385); return false;">Major Gordon</a></span>, translated by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/shfoakdls" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1411238); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1411238&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="shfoakdls" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1411238)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/shfoakdls" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1411238); return false;">shfoakdls</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2524">SCP-2524</a> (&quot;No Strings&quot;) - Why don't you come in? I saw something very interesting in your shadow, I thought you'd like to know&#8230; Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2038009&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="TyGently" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2038009)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;">TyGently</a></span>.</li>
